'''Dr. Taranath Sharma''' popular name '''Tana Sarma''' is a famous litterateur of [[Nepal]]. He is recognized as travel writer, essayist and [[literary critic]].<ref>People's Review Weekly (Thursday 20 March 2003)</ref> Dr. Sharma has authored over 112 books in [[Nepali language]].<ref name=tht>[http://www.thehimalayantimes.com/fullNews.php?headline=Man+of+his+words&NewsID=246113 Man of his words ] The Himalayan Times</ref> He has been contributing the Nepali Literature for over five decades.<ref name=kantipur>[http://www.ekantipur.com/2011/07/01/capital/litterateur-sharma-conferred-aadi-kabi-award/336624.html Litterateur Sharma conferred Aadi Kabi award] Kantipur Daily</ref>

Mr. Sharma has been awarded by various awards like [[Madan Puraskar]] Award 1969 for 'Belayat tira baralida' travelogue, Saajha Award 1972 for 'Sama ra samaka kriti' critic, and Aadi kabi Bhanubhakta award 2013.<ref name=kantipur />

Taranath Sharma was born on 23 June 1934 in Barbote [[Ilam District|Ilam]] as the first child of Mr. Prajapati Upadhyay a social reformer.<ref name=tht /> Quitting the [[Sanskrit]] education he continued his studies in the English school that was established by his father. He completed his school level studies at St Joseph's, [[Darjeeling]]. Sharma got PhD in Linguistics from the [[University of Wisconsin-Madison]] in the US.<ref name=tht />

While studying BA in [[Banaras]], he initiated the 'Jharro Nepali' a literature movement with his friends. He has written his first work, Ojhel Parda, in 1966 inside jail while he was imprisoned for criticizing late [[King Mahendra]]'s poem.<ref name=tht />

His travelogue entitled 'Belaittira Baralinda' meaning Ramblings in and around Britain, which he wrote while he was doing his Post Graduate Diploma with English as second language in the [[University College of North Wales]] won the popular 'Madan Puraskar' award in 1969.

Mr. Sharma has served as the editor in chief of [[The Rising Nepal]] English daily for some years after the restoration of democracy in [[Nepal]].

